>=20
> On vacation, with just an iPad keyboard, so I apologize for not doing =
more digging.  As I noted, when taking the blame for the Great Echo =
Schism, my early exposure to a hp2640 terminal that allowed =E2=80=9Crentr=
y=E2=80=9D of a previous command was partly to blame. It also led me to =
use a PS1 ending in @, the default line-kill. When I reentered a =
command, the @ wiped out the prompt stuff, and only the command =
survived.=20
>=20
