>=20
>> The prompt I have used since about 1997 (and I can't remember where I =
got
>> it from - somewhere on Usenet, probably) in its most distilled form =
is
>>=20
>> :;
>=20
> I forget where I stole this from. It lives in $home/lib/profile on my =
Plan9 machines:
>=20
> # /n/sources/contrib/lyndon/prompt.rc
> fn : {}
> fn setprompt {
>        prompt =3D (': '^`{cat /dev/user}^@^`{cat =
/dev/sysname}^':'^`{pwd}^'; '  '        ')
> }
> fn cd { builtin cd $* && setprompt }
> setprompt
>=20
