class=3D""></blockquote><br class=3D"">The es shell (by Haar and =
Rakitzis) used ; - the reason (as<br class=3D"">per the man page)is that =
a user can cut-n-paste a previous<br class=3D"">line to rexecute it (for =
the same reason people use term% and<br class=3D"">cpu% functions to =
execute their args). &nbsp;Es syntax was derived<br class=3D"">from rc, =
which may be why the confusion.<br class=3D""><br class=3D""><br =
